    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="9"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0012/532m</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMT1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-04">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>47. British Ambassador has been authorized to sign the treaty providing for
                    investigation in all cases. British and French treaties were to be signed the
                    same day. French treaty is ready, this Government <pb facs="0321" n="7"
                        xml:id="pg_7"/> having accepted and made all changes suggested in recent
                    telegram. Spanish Ambassador has also received instruction to sign treaty which
                    is now being prepared. Please urge upon the Government the advisability of
                    authorizing Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_JJAAJ1">Jusserand</persName> to
                    sign on day to be agreed upon between him and the British Ambassador. Twenty-two
                    treaties have already been signed. The British and French treaties are now
                    ready. The Spanish treaty will be ready to-morrow. Duplicate is being sent to
                    the Embassy at Bordeaux.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
